1. Feature Name
Hook Generator
2. Goal
Enable users to create compelling story openings by selecting from 5 proven hook types, generating AI-powered hook options tailored to their story context, and refining their chosen hook through editing. This feature ensures stories start strong by applying the Storyteller Tactics "Hook" framework to capture audience attention immediately.
3. User Story
As a user developing my story,
I want to generate and select from professionally-crafted opening hooks,
So that I can immediately capture my audience's attention and make them want to hear more.
4. Functional Requirements
4.1 Core Functionality

Display 5 hook types with clear explanations:

Unexpected: Contrarian, surprising, challenges assumptions
Knowledge: Expertise-based, insider information, "secrets of"
Story: Scene-based, action-oriented, drops into a moment
Question: Provocative questions, "what if" scenarios
Emotional: Relatable feelings, universal experiences


Multi-select capability: User can select 1-5 hook types to explore
AI generation: For each selected type, generate 3 hook options
Context-aware generation: Hooks reflect user's story type, audience, character, and conflict
Hook cards display:

The hook text itself (editable)
"Why this works" explanation (educational)
Tone indicator (conversational, dramatic, professional, etc.)
"Use this" button
"Refine this" button (inline editing)
"Regenerate" button (get new options)


Selection and saving: User selects one hook, saved to story state
Manual creation: Option to write hook from scratch
Preview mode: See how hook looks in context of full story opening

4.2 Hook Type Selection Interface
