4.4 Inline Editing ("Refine This")
When user clicks "Refine This":

Hook text becomes editable textarea
Character counter (recommend 100-200 characters)
Tone selector (adjust formality: casual/professional/dramatic)
AI assist button: "Make it more [surprising/emotional/concrete]"
Preview button: See in context
Save edits button
Revert button (back to AI original)

4.5 Hook Selection & Confirmation
When user clicks "Use This":

Highlight selected hook (visual checkmark, different background)
Deselect others (only one hook can be active)
Show preview: "Your story will begin: '[hook text]'"
Continue button appears (advances to next step)
Change selection allows switching to different hook

4.6 Manual Hook Creation

"Write My Own" button always visible
Opens blank textarea with guidance:

"Great hooks are typically 1-3 sentences"
"Consider: What's surprising? What creates curiosity?"
"What emotion do you want to evoke?"


AI coaching: Optional "Get suggestions" analyzes user's draft
Save when satisfied

4.7 State Management
javascriptstoryData.hooks = {
  selectedTypes: ['unexpected', 'knowledge', 'story'], // User's selections
  generated: {
    unexpected: [
      {
        id: 'unexp_1',
        text: 'We raised zero dollars...',
        whyItWorks: 'Challenges common narrative...',
        tone: 'provocative',
        isEdited: false,
        originalText: 'We raised zero dollars...'
      },
      // 2 more unexpected hooks
    ],
    knowledge: [...], // 3 knowledge hooks
    story: [...] // 3 story hooks
  },
  chosen: {
    id: 'unexp_1',
    type: 'unexpected',
    text: 'We raised zero dollars and it was the best decision...',
    isEdited: false,
    editHistory: []
  },
  manualHook: null, // If user writes from scratch
  generatedAt: timestamp,
  selectedAt: timestamp
};
