5.3 AI Generation Tracking
sql-- Track hook generation requests for analytics and rate limiting
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS hook_generations (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  story_id UUID REFERENCES stories(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  hook_types TEXT[], -- Array of requested types
  context JSONB, -- Story context sent to AI
  generated_count INTEGER, -- How many hooks generated
  selected_hook_id TEXT, -- Which hook was chosen
  generation_time_ms INTEGER, -- Performance tracking
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Index for user query
CREATE INDEX idx_hook_gen_user ON hook_generations(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_hook_gen_story ON hook_generations(story_id);
```

## 6. UI/UX Requirements

### 6.1 Visual Design

**Hook Type Selection Screen**:
- **Grid layout**: 5 cards in responsive grid (3 cols desktop, 2 tablet, 1 mobile)
- **Card design**: Each type has unique color accent (purple, blue, orange, green, red)
- **Checkbox selection**: Large, clear checkboxes with visual feedback
- **Icon prominence**: Large emoji icons (48px) at top of each card
- **Example preview**: Show 1 example hook in smaller text
- **Multi-select indication**: Selected cards have border highlight and checkmark

**Hook Results Screen**:
- **Grouped by type**: Clear visual separation between hook types
- **Card-based layout**: Each hook in its own card with subtle shadow
- **Scannable**: User can quickly read all options before deep dive
- **Edit state**: When editing, card expands slightly with edit controls
- **Selected state**: Chosen hook has distinct visual treatment (purple border, checkmark badge)

**Responsive Behavior**:
- **Desktop**: 2-column layout for hook cards, side-by-side comparison
- **Tablet**: Single column, full width cards
- **Mobile**: Stack vertically, sticky "Continue" button at bottom

